The paper deals with computational geometry problems such as closest pair, furthest pair, and orthogonal vectors, which are typically studied in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from data structures (cs.DS), complexity theory (cs.CC), and information theory (cs.IT) to prove lower bounds on the running time of certain algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the Orthogonal Vectors Conjecture, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
